  "text": "The We also see these tools as failing to support curation goals around impression management. Facebook's \"others see me as\" feature allows people to see themselves as others see them, at least through the Facebook Timeline, and in principle, this could be used to support impression management of past content. As a tool for helping people think about their image, however, this view is not very helpful. The system provides neither interpretation nor guidance, which are often important in tools designed to help people reflect on their behavior [CITATION_1] . In particular, it doesn't help people think about what might be important to consider in their image, nor specific ways their content might contribute to that image.",
